WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.150 --> 00:00:02.230
- Good morning, I hope
you're having an amazing day.

00:00:02.230 --> 00:00:04.080
It's Mark Wiens, I'm in Gilgit, Pakistan,

00:00:04.080 --> 00:00:05.820
and in the Karakoram Mountain Range.

00:00:05.820 --> 00:00:09.750
Today we are gonna go on a
cultural and food tour of Gilgit.

00:00:09.750 --> 00:00:11.540
We're gonna explore the market.

00:00:11.540 --> 00:00:14.320
We were invited to a
local home to eat lunch.

00:00:14.320 --> 00:00:17.110
I'm psyched to be here,
it's just spectacular.

00:00:17.110 --> 00:00:18.343
Okay, let's move.

00:00:19.641 --> 00:00:22.224
(upbeat music)

00:00:27.080 --> 00:00:29.170
All right, I'm gonna rewind
real fast to the day before.

00:00:29.170 --> 00:00:31.870
Our plan was to drive
through Deosai National Park

00:00:31.870 --> 00:00:34.680
on our way to Gilgit, but things
didn't work out as planned

00:00:34.680 --> 00:00:36.890
so we ended up having to turn around

00:00:36.890 --> 00:00:39.777
and make a very long drive
in the opposite direction

00:00:39.777 --> 00:00:40.700
to get to Gilgit.

00:00:40.700 --> 00:00:42.560
Before we start today's tour of Gilgit,

00:00:42.560 --> 00:00:44.670
I just wanna show you a
little bit of yesterday.

00:00:44.670 --> 00:00:46.210
We're not sure how much snow...

00:00:46.210 --> 00:00:49.320
It snowed last night, but we're
gonna go across the plains

00:00:49.320 --> 00:00:52.550
and try, attempt, to
get to the other side,

00:00:52.550 --> 00:00:54.450
and then make our way to Gilgit.

00:00:54.450 --> 00:00:55.620
Okay, getting kind of cold now,

00:00:55.620 --> 00:00:57.348
but we've stopped at Satpara Lake.

00:00:57.348 --> 00:00:58.921
(car engine revving)

00:00:58.921 --> 00:01:00.763
(car door closes)

00:01:00.763 --> 00:01:03.346
(upbeat music)

00:01:07.314 --> 00:01:10.720
(car engine roars)

00:01:10.720 --> 00:01:11.631
It's snowing.

00:01:11.631 --> 00:01:12.876
(laughing)

00:01:12.876 --> 00:01:15.112
- [Ali] This is the
starting point of Deosai.

00:01:15.112 --> 00:01:17.060
This is the starting point
of Deosai National Park.

00:01:17.060 --> 00:01:17.903
- Sweet.

00:01:19.528 --> 00:01:21.390
(laughing)

00:01:21.390 --> 00:01:22.230
Got a bit of...

00:01:22.230 --> 00:01:25.100
Got a bit of a dilemma.

00:01:25.100 --> 00:01:27.442
Okay, my lips are starting to freeze.

00:01:27.442 --> 00:01:29.670
- This place is like 12,000 feet,

00:01:29.670 --> 00:01:32.610
and it's gonna be 14,000 feet
once we get to Sheosar Lake.

00:01:32.610 --> 00:01:33.760
- And it's gonna be snowing harder?

00:01:33.760 --> 00:01:35.533
- Certainly harder, it's
gonna take the elevation

00:01:35.533 --> 00:01:37.510
2,000 more feet.

00:01:37.510 --> 00:01:40.260
- We're not sure if we should
pass all the way through.

00:01:41.820 --> 00:01:44.660
I mean, if it's not safe
then let's not risk it.

00:01:44.660 --> 00:01:46.170
That's just fresh powder.

00:01:46.170 --> 00:01:48.223
That's, like, snow cone, cheers.

00:01:51.033 --> 00:01:52.879
Did you eat some snow?

00:01:52.879 --> 00:01:54.155
Oh, that's cold.

00:01:54.155 --> 00:01:56.738
(upbeat music)

00:02:03.500 --> 00:02:06.690
The chicken boti kebabs are on the grill.

00:02:06.690 --> 00:02:08.543
It smells so good.

00:02:08.543 --> 00:02:10.690
(speaking in foreign language)

00:02:10.690 --> 00:02:11.523
Oh, nice.

00:02:19.365 --> 00:02:20.198
Oh, wow.

00:02:20.198 --> 00:02:21.530
Back in the car now, we're
on our way to Gilgit.

00:02:21.530 --> 00:02:24.554
We still, I'm sure, have about
three or four hours left.

00:02:24.554 --> 00:02:26.550
(upbeat music)

00:02:26.550 --> 00:02:28.750
Okay, so it is midnight.

00:02:28.750 --> 00:02:31.830
We've been driving since
6:30 a.m. this morning.

00:02:31.830 --> 00:02:33.810
We finally arrived to Gilgit.

00:02:33.810 --> 00:02:35.186
Thank you, nice to meet you.

00:02:35.186 --> 00:02:36.497
(speaking in foreign language)

00:02:36.497 --> 00:02:38.500
- [Woman] This is homemade
crepe and fritter.

00:02:38.500 --> 00:02:41.083
(upbeat music)

00:02:42.785 --> 00:02:45.709
(laughing)

00:02:45.709 --> 00:02:49.770
- They prepared dinner for us,
and we got here kind of late,

00:02:49.770 --> 00:02:53.713
but they've graciously still
served us dinner at 1:00 a.m.

00:02:54.730 --> 00:02:56.343
Okay, next up for a local soup.

00:03:00.640 --> 00:03:02.445
It's so juicy.

00:03:02.445 --> 00:03:05.028
(upbeat music)

00:03:12.060 --> 00:03:12.893
Thank you.

00:03:14.106 --> 00:03:16.689
(upbeat music)

00:03:23.450 --> 00:03:25.240
Welcome to the center of Gilgit,

00:03:25.240 --> 00:03:27.640
it's a bustling little city
but actually quite calm.

00:03:27.640 --> 00:03:29.190
The air is fresh.

00:03:29.190 --> 00:03:30.930
Actually we're driving in the van,

00:03:30.930 --> 00:03:34.570
but we just noticed this giant
pot of food right up ahead,

00:03:34.570 --> 00:03:36.280
and that's actually the
reason why we stopped.

00:03:36.280 --> 00:03:37.190
We gotta see what's in there.

00:03:37.190 --> 00:03:40.610
But just take a look at this truck.

00:03:40.610 --> 00:03:42.380
Fully outfitted for the mountains.

00:03:42.380 --> 00:03:43.560
They're loading it up.

00:03:43.560 --> 00:03:45.398
There's garlic and vegetables on the top.

00:03:45.398 --> 00:03:46.948
Look at that detail.

00:03:46.948 --> 00:03:50.750
(speaking in foreign language)

00:03:50.750 --> 00:03:53.640
I love how it's topped in
a leopard print blanket.

00:03:53.640 --> 00:03:56.023
Oh, nice, he just opened it up.

00:03:57.693 --> 00:03:59.300
Oh, that aroma, yeah, it's huge.

00:03:59.300 --> 00:04:00.820
And it looks like such fluffy rice.

00:04:00.820 --> 00:04:02.460
So it is Kabuli pulao.

00:04:02.460 --> 00:04:03.670
He dishes you a plate,

00:04:03.670 --> 00:04:05.660
and then he scoops on a bunch of yogurt

00:04:05.660 --> 00:04:07.950
with tomatoes and onions
and cucumber inside.

00:04:07.950 --> 00:04:09.150
Yeah, what a cool spot.

00:04:09.150 --> 00:04:12.040
And, he's just, like, it's
in this closet-little shop.

00:04:12.040 --> 00:04:15.140
The master pot, it takes up
the entire front entrance

00:04:15.140 --> 00:04:16.400
of the entire shop,

00:04:16.400 --> 00:04:18.750
and then there's some
dark seating in the back.

00:04:25.110 --> 00:04:27.570
It's so light and fluffy,

00:04:27.570 --> 00:04:29.180
like the cinnamon-y spices.

00:04:29.180 --> 00:04:31.740
- Warm rice underneath,
and the cool yogurt

00:04:31.740 --> 00:04:35.340
and the crunch from the
onions, that's really nice.

00:04:35.340 --> 00:04:37.880
- Yeah, that fresh vegetable-like yogurt.

00:04:37.880 --> 00:04:40.340
Vegetable-filled yogurt.

00:04:40.340 --> 00:04:41.173
Thank you.

00:04:46.224 --> 00:04:47.916
- [Mark] Get that yogurt on that.

00:04:47.916 --> 00:04:50.190
(speaking in foreign language)

00:04:50.190 --> 00:04:51.500
Oh, yeah, it would be good, though.

00:04:51.500 --> 00:04:53.590
Okay, Ali is just asking
for a piece of meat.

00:04:53.590 --> 00:04:55.290
Thanks to Ali we got the meat hookup.

00:04:55.290 --> 00:04:56.760
He asked him for some extra meat there,

00:04:56.760 --> 00:04:58.080
because there's not a
lot of meat in the dish,

00:04:58.080 --> 00:05:00.250
mostly used just for
flavor, to flavor the dish,

00:05:00.250 --> 00:05:02.920
but we did get a couple chunks
plus some more of that raita,

00:05:02.920 --> 00:05:05.233
that's the yogurt sauce
with the vegetables in it.

00:05:08.020 --> 00:05:09.583
Oh, the meat, yum.

00:05:12.100 --> 00:05:13.951
And bathing in steam of the pot.

00:05:13.951 --> 00:05:15.201
- He's eating in the car.

00:05:16.402 --> 00:05:18.263
(horn honking)

00:05:18.263 --> 00:05:20.763
(chill beats)

00:05:21.890 --> 00:05:23.823
- The one over here is beef sliver.

00:05:27.238 --> 00:05:29.680
(speaking in foreign language)

00:05:29.680 --> 00:05:31.200
- We stopped at the next stall.

00:05:31.200 --> 00:05:33.010
We saw... it's beef.

00:05:33.010 --> 00:05:35.220
It looks so beautifully
marinated with chilis

00:05:35.220 --> 00:05:37.720
and some kind of a red something.

00:05:37.720 --> 00:05:40.170
How can you resist a stall
that looks like this?

00:05:40.170 --> 00:05:41.530
We got also some chutney,

00:05:41.530 --> 00:05:42.960
but let me just taste that straight meat.

00:05:42.960 --> 00:05:44.350
This is right off the grill.

00:05:44.350 --> 00:05:46.680
You just bite it right off the skewer.

00:05:46.680 --> 00:05:47.513
It's dripping.

00:05:49.730 --> 00:05:51.844
That's like salty, you
taste the chilis in there.

00:05:51.844 --> 00:05:52.963
That's some good meat.

00:05:54.462 --> 00:05:55.670
(dishes clanging)

00:05:55.670 --> 00:05:58.485
(car horn honking)

00:05:58.485 --> 00:06:00.450
And that chutney, I don't
know what that chutney is.

00:06:00.450 --> 00:06:01.350
There's, like, lumps in it.

00:06:01.350 --> 00:06:03.100
It's kind of, like, yogurt-y maybe.

00:06:05.760 --> 00:06:08.060
The chutney is kind of plain,
maybe a little chili in there.

00:06:08.060 --> 00:06:10.700
And I think that is yogurt, maybe.

00:06:10.700 --> 00:06:14.230
Again, dip it in that
chunky, curdled chutney.

00:06:14.230 --> 00:06:16.313
Never had a chutney like that before.

00:06:18.980 --> 00:06:21.714
Oh, yeah, all the liver is great.

00:06:21.714 --> 00:06:24.750
(upbeat music)

00:06:24.750 --> 00:06:27.210
We haven't even made it to
the main bazaar, main market.

00:06:27.210 --> 00:06:28.120
That's where...

00:06:28.120 --> 00:06:29.770
We're on our way there right now.

00:06:30.624 --> 00:06:33.124
(chill beats)

00:06:34.260 --> 00:06:37.390
You just will not be able
to get over, to fathom,

00:06:37.390 --> 00:06:40.640
the views from the city, just
the mountains surrounding,

00:06:40.640 --> 00:06:45.030
and just, like, the most
rugged, jagged, steep cliffs

00:06:45.030 --> 00:06:46.630
of any mountains I've ever seen.

00:06:47.708 --> 00:06:50.940
And just snow-covered,
capped mountains everywhere.

00:06:50.940 --> 00:06:54.053
(speaking in foreign language)

00:06:54.053 --> 00:06:55.928
I just got the full spectrum.

00:06:55.928 --> 00:06:57.800
(speaking in foreign language)

00:06:57.800 --> 00:06:59.380
Thank you, it's so good.

00:07:05.348 --> 00:07:08.672
(chill music)

00:07:08.672 --> 00:07:11.050
Oh, that looks so good.

00:07:11.050 --> 00:07:13.941
Again, just a total unplanned stop.

00:07:13.941 --> 00:07:17.100
The man selling the curry, he
actually was smiling at Micah

00:07:17.100 --> 00:07:19.520
and waving at Smile with this huge grin.

00:07:19.520 --> 00:07:20.630
What an amazing man.

00:07:20.630 --> 00:07:22.030
You couldn't resist the chaplis?

00:07:22.030 --> 00:07:22.871
- Yup.
- No.

00:07:22.871 --> 00:07:23.911
(laughing)

00:07:23.911 --> 00:07:25.655
- [Ali] How could a day go
by without having chaplis?

00:07:25.655 --> 00:07:27.450
- [Mark] When a day can
go by without chaplis.

00:07:27.450 --> 00:07:29.600
- When we walked up,
though, he was like...

00:07:30.546 --> 00:07:33.213
(food sizzling)

00:07:34.820 --> 00:07:36.580
- Oh, it's like a doughnut.

00:07:36.580 --> 00:07:39.360
And Uncle has this amazing
little dining room.

00:07:39.360 --> 00:07:41.710
Check out this little
closet-sized dining room.

00:07:43.380 --> 00:07:44.570
We're gonna sit in here.

00:07:44.570 --> 00:07:46.070
Okay, we got the chapli kebab.

00:07:47.180 --> 00:07:48.790
This is such a cool little spot,

